<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Title</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="${yaml_base_css}"></link>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="${base_css}"></link>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="${scrollbar_style_base}"></link>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="${scrollbar_style_laf}"></link>
  <style>
    ${typography_color_style}
  </style>
</head>
<body>
<br>
YAML format was introduced to make course configuration easier and transparent.
Now it's possible to change the course structure by editing <span class="config">*.yaml</span> files.
Here's a description of the format for each course item.
<br> <br>

<h3>Course</h3>
<div class="description"><span class="config">course-info.yaml</span> describes the structure of a course:</div>

<table class="yaml-format-table">
  <tbody>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Description</th>
    <th>Value</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>title</td>
    <td>Title of the course</td>
    <td>String</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>language</td>
    <td>Languages used for course materials</td>
    <td>Any of supported languages, e.g. <span class="enum">English</span>,
      <span class="enum">German</span>,
      <span class="enum">French</span>,
      <span class="enum">Spanish</span>,
      <span class="enum">Russian</span>, etc.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>summary</td>
    <td>Summary describing what the course is about</td>
    <td>String</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>programming_language</td>
    <td>Programming language of the course</td>
    <td>Any of supported programming languages, e.g.
      <span class="enum">Java</span>,
      <span class="enum">Kotlin</span>,
      <span class="enum">Scala</span>,
      <span class="enum">JavaScript</span>,
      <span class="enum">Rust</span>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>programming_language_version</td>
    <td>Optional version of programming language</td>
    <td>Number or String</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>environment</td>
    <td>Additional information about the course environment</td>
    <td>
      For example, Kotlin courses are supported for Android environment
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>content</td>
    <td>Directory names of lessons or sections included in the course</td>
    <td>List of directory names</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>solutions_hidden</td>
    <td>If solutions are available for learners to peek and compare with their answers</td>
    <td><span class="enum">true</span> or <span class="enum">false</span><br>
      Default: <span class="enum">true</span>
    </td>
  </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h3>Section</h3>
<div class="description"><span class="config">section-info.yaml</span> describes the structure of a section:</div>

<table class="yaml-format-table">
  <tbody>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Description</th>
    <th>Value</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>custom_name</td>
    <td>Custom name for the section if it differs from its directory name.
      Useful when you need to use a symbol that is not allowed in directory names, for example, &quot;:&quot;.
    </td>
    <td>String</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>content</td>
    <td>directory names of the lessons included in the section</td>
    <td>List of directory names</td>
  </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Lesson</h3>
<div class="description"><span class="config">lesson-info.yaml</span> describes the structure of a lesson:
</div>


<table class="yaml-format-table">
  <tbody>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Description</th>
    <th>Value</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>type</td>
    <td>Lesson type</td>
    <td><span class="enum">lesson</span><br>
      <span class="enum">framework</span>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>custom_name</td>
    <td>Custom name for the lesson if it differs from its directory name.
      Useful when you need to use a symbol that is not allowed in directory names, for example, &quot;:&quot;.
    </td>
    <td>String</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>content</td>
    <td>Directory names of tasks included in the section</td>
    <td>List of directory names</td>
  </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Task</h3>
<div class="description"><span class="config">task-info.yaml</span> describes the structure of a task:
</div>

<table class="yaml-format-table">
  <tbody>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Description</th>
    <th>Value</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>type</td>
    <td>Task type</td>
    <td><span class="enum">edu</span>
      <span class="enum">theory</span>
      <span class="enum">output</span>
      <span class="enum">ide</span>
      <span class="enum">code</span>
      <span class="enum">choice</span>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>custom_name</td>
    <td>Custom name for the task if it differs from its directory name.
      Useful when you need to use a symbol that is not allowed in directory names, for example, &quot;:&quot;.
    </td>
    <td>String</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>files</td>
    <td>Files included in the task</td>
    <td>List of <span class="enum">files</span> in format described below</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>feedback_link</td>
    <td>Custom link for learners to leave their feedback about the task</td>
    <td>E.g., Google Forms link</td>
  </tr>

  <tr>
    <td>is_multiple_choice</td>
    <td>If <span class="enum">choice</span> task allows multiple correct answers</td>
    <td><span class="enum">true</span> <span class="enum">false</span></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>message_correct</td>
    <td><span class="enum">choice</span> Custom message to be shown to learner in case of correct solution</td>
    <td>E.g., &quot;reat job!&quot; or &quot;Fantastic!&quot;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>message_incorrect</td>
    <td>
      <span class="enum">choice</span> Custom message to be shown to learner in case of incorrect solution
    </td>
    <td>E.g., &quot;Review how to define a function to solve this task&quot;</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>options</td>
    <td><span class="enum">choice</span> task answer variants</td>
    <td>List of options. Option has two parameters: <span class="enum">text</span> and <span class="enum">is_correct</span></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>solution_hidden</td>
    <td>If solution is available for learners to peek and compare with their answer</td>
    <td><span class="enum">true</span> or <span class="enum">false</span><br>
      Default: <span class="enum">true</span>
    </td>
  </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


<h4 id="file-format"><span class="enum">file</span> format</h4>
<table class="yaml-format-table">
  <tbody>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Description</th>
    <th>Value</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>name</td>
    <td>File path relative to the directory of the task</td>
    <td>String</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>visible</td>
    <td>If the file is shown to learner or not</td>
    <td><span class="enum">true</span> <span class="enum">false</span></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>placeholders</td>
    <td>Answer placeholders</td>
    <td>List of <span class="enum">placeholders</span> in format described below</td>
  </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h4 id="placeholder-format"><span class="enum">placeholder</span> structure</h4>
<table class="yaml-format-table">
  <tbody>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Description</th>
    <th>Value</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>offset</td>
    <td>Placeholder start offset</td>
    <td>Number</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>length</td>
    <td>Placeholder length</td>
    <td>Number</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>placeholder_text</td>
    <td>Text which will be shown to learner in place of the placeholder</td>
    <td>String</td>
  </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>


</body>
</html>